Federated Learning is an approach for learning algorithms where data is distributed across multiple compute devices connected to a (federated) central server system through a
secure communications channel.

This tool is used to distribute machine learning algorithms to extract knowledge from data on demand. We (i.e. this tool) recommend moving data to a central server for computations.

Benefits

* Reduces the amount of data stored locally
* Deeper analytics by leveraging more data
* Shortage of infrastructure for local inference
